Process called "h264_signature" returns ByteArray:
    Return ByteArray.from_bytes with bytes as list containing 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01

Process called "h265_signature" returns ByteArray:
    Return ByteArray.from_bytes with bytes as list containing 0x00, 0x00, 0x00, 0x01, 0x40

Process called "vp9_signature" returns ByteArray:
    Return ByteArray.from_bytes with bytes as list containing 0x82, 0x49, 0x83, 0x42

Process called "av1_signature" returns ByteArray:
    Return ByteArray.from_bytes with bytes as list containing 0x0A, 0x0B

Note: Platform integration helper functions
Type called "PacketHeader":
    width as Integer
    height as Integer
    pixel_format as String

Process called "analyze_packet_header" that takes data as ByteArray and codec as VideoCodec returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Basic header analysis for common codecs
    Match codec:
        When H264:
            Return analyze_h264_header with data as data
        When H265:
            Return analyze_h265_header with data as data
        When VP9:
            Return analyze_vp9_header with data as data
        When AV1:
            Return analyze_av1_header with data as data
        Otherwise:
            Return PacketHeader with:
                width as 1920
                height as 1080
                pixel_format as "RGB24"

Process called "analyze_h264_header" that takes data as ByteArray returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Parse H.264 SPS (Sequence Parameter Set) for dimensions
    If data.size() is greater than 8:
        Note: Look for SPS NAL unit (0x67)
        For i from 0 to data.size() minus 4:
            If data.get_byte with index as i is equal to 0x00 and data.get_byte with index as i 1 is equal to 0x00 and data.get_byte with index as i 2 is equal to 0x00 and data.get_byte with index as i 3 is equal to 0x01:
                If i 4 is less than data.size() and data.get_byte with index as i 4 is equal to 0x67:
                    Return extract_h264_dimensions with sps_data as data.slice with start as i 5 and length as minimum with a as 32 and b as data.size() minus i - 5
    
    Return PacketHeader with:
        width as 1920
        height as 1080
        pixel_format as "YUV420P"

Process called "analyze_h265_header" that takes data as ByteArray returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Parse H.265 SPS for dimensions
    Return PacketHeader with:
        width as 1920
        height as 1080
        pixel_format as "YUV420P"

Process called "analyze_vp9_header" that takes data as ByteArray returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Parse VP9 frame header
    If data.size() is greater than 4:
        Let frame_marker be data.get_byte with index as 0 divided by 192
        If frame_marker is equal to 2:
            Note: Valid VP9 frame
            Return PacketHeader with:
                width as 1920
                height as 1080
                pixel_format as "YUV420P"
    
    Return PacketHeader with:
        width as 1920
        height as 1080
        pixel_format as "YUV420P"

Process called "analyze_av1_header" that takes data as ByteArray returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Parse AV1 frame header
    Return PacketHeader with:
        width as 1920
        height as 1080
        pixel_format as "YUV420P"

Process called "extract_h264_dimensions" that takes sps_data as ByteArray returns PacketHeader:
    Note: Parse H.264 SPS (Sequence Parameter Set) for video dimensions
    Let reader be create_bit_reader with data as sps_data
    
    Note: Skip NAL header byte if present
    If sps_data.size is greater than 0 and (sps_data.data at index 0) is equal to 0x67:
        Call advance_bits with reader as reader and bits as 8
    
    Note: Skip profile_idc, constraint_set flags, level_idc
    Call advance_bits with reader as reader and bits as 24
    
    Note: Read seq_parameter_set_id using Exp-Golomb
    Let sps_id be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
    
    Note: Handle different profile_idc values
    Let profile_idc be sps_data.data at index 1
    If profile_idc is equal to 100 or profile_idc is equal to 110 or profile_idc is equal to 122 or profile_idc is equal to 244:
        Note: High profile - read chroma format
        Let chroma_format_idc be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
        If chroma_format_idc is equal to 3:
            Call advance_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1
        Let bit_depth_luma be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 8
        Let bit_depth_chroma be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 8
        Call advance_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1
    
    Note: Read frame dimensions
    Let log2_max_frame_num be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 4
    Let pic_order_cnt_type be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
    
    Note: Skip POC parameters based on type
    If pic_order_cnt_type is equal to 0:
        Let log2_max_pic_order_cnt be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 4
    Otherwise if pic_order_cnt_type is equal to 1:
        Call advance_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1
        Let offset_for_non_ref_pic be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
        Let offset_for_top_to_bottom be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
        Let num_ref_frames_in_cycle be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
    
    Let max_num_ref_frames be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader
    Let gaps_in_frame_num be read_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1
    
    Note: Read actual dimensions in macroblocks
    Let pic_width_in_mbs be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 1
    Let pic_height_in_map_units be read_exp_golomb with reader as reader plus 1
    
    Note: Convert macroblocks to pixels (16x16 pixels per macroblock)
    Let width be pic_width_in_mbs times 16
    Let height be pic_height_in_map_units times 16
    
    Note: Check for frame/field coding
    Let frame_mbs_only be read_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1
    If frame_mbs_only is equal to 0:
        Set height to height times 2
    
    Return PacketHeader with:
        width as width
        height as height
        pixel_format as "YUV420P"

Process called "get_bytes_per_pixel" that takes format as String returns Integer:
    Match format:
        When "RGB24":
            Return 3
        When "RGBA32":
            Return 4
        When "YUV420P":
            Return 1.5 as Integer
        When "YUV444P":
            Return 3
        When "GRAY8":
            Return 1
        Otherwise:
            Return 3

Process called "maximum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is greater than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Process called "minimum" that takes a as Integer and b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is less than b:
        Return a
    Return b

Note: Export public APIs
Note: Bit reading and Exp-Golomb helper functions

Type called "BitReader":
    data as ByteArray
    byte_position as Integer
    bit_position as Integer

Process called "create_bit_reader" that takes data as ByteArray returns BitReader:
    Return BitReader with:
        data as data
        byte_position as 0
        bit_position as 0

Process called "read_bits" that takes reader as BitReader and bits as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Read specified number of bits from the stream
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to bits minus 1:
        Let byte_idx be reader.byte_position
        Let bit_idx be reader.bit_position
        
        If byte_idx is less than reader.data.size:
            Let byte_val be reader.data.data at index byte_idx
            Let bit_val be (byte_val right_shift (7 minus bit_idx)) bitwise_and 1
            Set result to (result left_shift 1) bitwise_or bit_val
        
        Set reader.bit_position to reader.bit_position plus 1
        If reader.bit_position is equal to 8:
            Set reader.bit_position to 0
            Set reader.byte_position to reader.byte_position plus 1
    
    Return result

Process called "advance_bits" that takes reader as BitReader and bits as Integer:
    Note: Skip specified number of bits in the stream
    For i from 0 to bits minus 1:
        Set reader.bit_position to reader.bit_position plus 1
        If reader.bit_position is equal to 8:
            Set reader.bit_position to 0
            Set reader.byte_position to reader.byte_position plus 1

Process called "read_exp_golomb" that takes reader as BitReader returns Integer:
    Note: Read Exponential-Golomb coded integer
    Let leading_zeros be 0
    
    Note: Count leading zero bits
    While read_bits with reader as reader and bits as 1 is equal to 0:
        Set leading_zeros to leading_zeros plus 1
        If leading_zeros is greater than 32:
            Return 0
    
    Note: Read the value bits
    If leading_zeros is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    
    Let value_bits be read_bits with reader as reader and bits as leading_zeros
    Return (1 left_shift leading_zeros) minus 1 plus value_bits

